n over shift stints. An impact estimate, not a box score."}, "offense": {"receipts": [{"label": "Offensive xG impact (RAPM)", "value": "-0.07 xG/60", "tone": "neg", "strong": true}, {"label": "On-ice xG created", "value": "32", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Relative on-ice xG%", "value": "-2.5%", "tone": "neg"}], "summary": "His effect on the chances his team CREATES at 5-on-5 \u2014 how much shot-quality (expected goals) his line generates with him out there, after adjusting for who he plays with and against.", "method": "His share of 5v5 expected-goals creation, adjusted for who he plays with and against."}, "defense": {"receipts": [{"label": "Defensive xG impact (RAPM)", "value": "-0.02 xG/60", "tone": "neutral", "strong": true}, {"label": "On-ice xG allowed", "value": "32", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "His effect on the chances his team ALLOWS at 5-on-5 \u2014 how well shot-quality against is held down with him on the ice, after adjusting for teammates and competition. A higher grade means fewer good chances against.", "method": "His suppression of 5v5 expected goals against, teammate- and competition-adjusted. Higher means fewer chances allowed while he's on the ice."}, "ppOffense": {"receipts": [{"label": "Power-play xG impact (RAPM)", "value": "-0.03 xG/60", "tone": "neutral", "strong": true}, {"label": "PP ice time", "value": "149 min", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "His impact on the POWER PLAY \u2014 how much his team's chances improve with him on the man advantage, graded only against players who actually log power-play minutes (so a bottom-six grinder isn't penalized for never being out there).", "method": "Power-play expected-goals impact, RAPM-adjusted. Graded vs peers who actually play the PP."}, "finishing": {"receipts": [{"label": "Career shots", "value": "3,631", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Goals", "value": "368", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Goals above cell-expected", "value": "+8.2", "tone": "pos"}, {"label": "Finishing / 100 shots",